text: Val-Couesnon is a commune in the Ille-et-Vilaine department in the Brittany in northwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Antrain (the seat), La Fontenelle, Saint-Ouen-la-Rouërie and Tremblay.Arrêté préfectoral 28 September 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Ille-et-Vilaine department ==References== Category:Communes of Ille-et- Vilaine
title: Val-Couesnon
